---
alwaysApply: true
---
version: 1
rules:
  - id: project-overview
    pattern: "*"
    description: |
      You are assisting in building a Project-Centric ERP system for the service industry.
      The system follows a Django-based backend architecture and SQL Server database.
      The design style, folder structure, and app separation should reference:
      https://github.com/DavidBloomer11/Bloomerp/tree/main.

      All code, migrations, models, and project organization must follow Django best practices.

      The system includes the following major modules:
        • Project Planning & Scheduling
        • Human Resource Allocation
        • Budgeting & Cost Estimation
        • Client Information Management (CRM-lite)
        • Resource Performance Analytics
        • AI Assistant (using genmini model) to:
            – Analyze resource performance
            – Recommend improvements for sales/purchasing
            – Suggest optimal project staffing
            – Recommend reasonable spending patterns based on charts

      The system must support multi-project management, time tracking,
      resource cost attribution, performance scoring, and financial summaries.

      The final system must be production-ready, scalable, maintainable, and modular.


  - id: technical-stack
    pattern: "*"
    description: |
      The system stack is strictly defined as:

      BACKEND:
        • Django (latest stable version)
        • Django REST Framework if API is needed
        • Authentication: Django built-in or DRF Token/JWT
        • Scheduling library: django-apscheduler (if required)
      
      DATABASE:
        • Microsoft SQL Server (connected via django-mssql-backend or mssql-django)
      
      AI MODEL:
        • genmini model (use official API client)
        • All AI-related functionalities must be encapsulated inside `/ai/` Django app
      
      FRONTEND:
        • Django Templates OR React/Next.js (but still served from Django if needed)
        • UI style follows Bloomerp structure:
          /templates
          /static/css
          /static/js
        • Layout should be minimal, modern, business-oriented.
      
      DEPLOYMENT:
        • Docker container for backend and frontend
        • Nginx reverse proxy
        • Gunicorn for Django
        • `.env` configuration for secrets


  - id: folder-structure
    pattern: "*"
    description: |
      Always generate code that fits this Django folder structure:

      /erp/
        manage.py
        /erp/ (main config)
        /core/ (base utilities, enums, helpers)
        /projects/ (manage project modules)
        /resources/ (HR and staff allocation)
        /budgeting/ (budgeting, cost tracking)
        /clients/ (CRM-like)
        /performance/ (performance and scoring analytics)
        /ai/ (AI assistant using genmini)
        /static/
        /templates/
        /scripts/ (database init, ETL, helpers)
        /docker/
        requirements.txt

      Each app must contain:
        models.py
        views.py
        forms.py
        urls.py
        serializers.py (if DRF used)
        services.py (business logic)
        tasks.py (if scheduled jobs)

      SQL Server migrations must be stable and compatible.


  - id: coding-standards
    pattern: "*.py"
    description: |
      Follow Python + Django best practices:
        • Class-based Views for webpages
        • DRF ViewSets for APIs
        • Use services.py to separate business logic
        • Use repositories (query wrapper classes) when needed
        • Use PEP8 formatting
        • Do not put heavy logic inside views
        • Always validate user input with forms or serializers

      Models must include:
        • created_at
        • updated_at
        • created_by (optional)
        • updated_by (optional)


  - id: ai-module
    pattern: "*/ai/*"
    description: |
      This module integrates genmini model.

      Required functionalities:
        • Analyze resource performance from DB metrics
        • Recommend project resource allocation
        • Provide suggestions for purchasing/sales improvements
        • Suggest budget optimization plans
        • Summaries and insights for dashboards

      AI interactions must:
        • Use a dedicated service class `ai/services.py`
        • Handle errors gracefully
        • Never block main request thread (async if needed)
        • Accept context such as:
            - Employee performance
            - Project workload
            - Budget trends
            - Financial charts
            - CRM data
        • Produce structured responses in JSON format:
            {
              "summary": "",
              "insights": [],
              "recommendations": []
            }


  - id: ui-guidelines
    pattern: "*.html"
    description: |
      Frontend UI must follow minimal business ERP design.
      References to the Bloomerp style:
        • Clean and structured layout
        • Sidebar navigation
        • Card-based dashboard
        • Light/Dark mode optional
      Required template structure:
        /templates/base.html
        /templates/components/
        /templates/pages/

      Use:
        • TailwindCSS or Bootstrap (only one)
        • Highcharts/Chart.js for interactive charts
        • Responsive layout


  - id: chart-logic
    pattern: "*"
    description: |
      All charts used in dashboards must be generated through:
        - Chart.js OR Highcharts (preferred)
      
      Data passed to graphs must be processed through Django services.
      AI recommendations must appear in a dashboard panel named:
      **"AI Assistant Insights"**.


  - id: sqlserver
    pattern: "*"
    description: |
      Always generate database code fully compatible with Microsoft SQL Server.
      Use:
        ENGINE = 'mssql'
        OPTIONS:
          driver: 'ODBC Driver 17 for SQL Server'
      
      Avoid:
        • JSONField (use TextField instead)
        • ArrayField
        • Postgres-only functions
        • Unsupported ORM features

      When writing raw SQL:
        Must be ANSI SQL, not Postgres-specific.


  - id: docker-rules
    pattern: "*Dockerfile*"
    description: |
      Use Python 3.11+
      Should include:
        - pip install -r requirements.txt
        - gunicorn for production
      Keep image minimal and secure.


  - id: generate-code
    pattern: "*"
    description: |
      When asked to generate code, always output:
        • Full file content (not partial snippets)
        • Correct imports
        • Path relative to the root of the project
        • Consistent naming
        • Ready-to-run Django code

      If user requests many modules at once:
        Generate in logical order:
          models → serializers → services → views → urls → templates


  - id: no-placeholder
    pattern: "*"
    description: |
      Do not output placeholder text like:
        "Add your logic here"
        "Implement this later"
      Everything must be real, working, meaningful code.


  - id: language-and-style
    pattern: "*"
    description: |
      The user prefers clear and professional Vietnamese.
      All explanations must be:
        • Ngắn gọn
        • Dễ hiểu
        • Theo phong cách technical documentation

